Name: herpes simplex virus keratitis
Definition: A keratitis that has_material_basis_in herpes simplex type infection.

Name: corneal neovascularization
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection due to migrating immature worms of Gnathostoma spinigerum or Gnathostoma hispidum

Name: macular keratitis
Definition: A leprosy that is an early form of the disease which causes one to a few hypopigmented or erythematous macules.

Name: obsolete Staphylococcus aureus septicemia
Definition: A leprosy that is an early form of the disease which causes one to a few hypopigmented or erythematous macules.

Name: obsolete staphylococcal septicemia
Definition: A leprosy that is an early form of the disease which causes one to a few hypopigmented or erythematous macules.

Name: superficial keratitis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the bile ducts of the liver by Dicrocoelium dendriticum. The symptoms include cholecystitis

Name: photokeratitis
Definition: A staphylococcal infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine caused by staphylococci

Name: filamentary keratitis
Definition: A brain disease that is characterized by Dejerine-Roussy syndrome that develops from thalamic injury.

Name: obsolete superficial keratitis without conjunctivitis
Definition: A brain disease that is characterized by Dejerine-Roussy syndrome that develops from thalamic injury.

Name: obsolete kyphosis
Definition: A bone structure disease that has_material_basis_in an abnormal curvature located_in vertebral column.

Name: obsolete congenital kyphosis
Definition: A kyphosis that results_in abnormal formation located_in body of vertebra.

Name: corneal ulcer
Definition: A syndrome that is characterized by absence or underdeveloped tissue connecting the left and right halves of the brain

Name: gonococcal keratitis
Definition: An acute myocarditis that is characterized by an underlying toxin insult to the myocardium that induces acute inflammation.

Name: deep keratitis
Definition: A connective tissue disease characterized by corneal scarring that develops from non-suppurative inflammation located_in the corneal stroma
